# Intralox Inline Tailwind Refactor (IT-INLINE)

**Client rule (Intralox):** Tailwind classes **inside JSX**; **`cn()` for conditional assignments**; **no constants** and **no separate style files** unless Tailwind cannot be applied on the JSX node.

## Required

- Static layout/presentation: `className="flex gap-4 …"` on the JSX element
- Conditionals (CMS params, state, theme): `className={cn('flex …', isActive && 'bg-surface', params.styles)}` on the **same node**
- Utils: **data only** — field parsing, visibility, labels, test ids (not Tailwind strings)
- Design tokens: `@theme` utilities (`bg-surface`, `text-ink-primary`), not raw hex

## Prohibited

- Top-level `const FOO_CLASS = '…'` in any `.tsx` (private or exported)
- `export const *_CLASS` / `*_CLASS_MAP` in `.tsx`
- `*Classes.ts` and class strings in `*Utils.ts` (`getXClass`, `buildXClassName`, maps)
- `className={SOME_CONST}` — use inline literal or inline `cn()` instead
- New component SCSS / CSS modules for layout, color, or typography

## Allowed exceptions (rare — document in PR with reason)

| Exception | When |
|-----------|------|
| Separate style module | **Only** when Tailwind cannot be placed on JSX (e.g. third-party root without `className`, legacy global SXA override that cannot be beaten inline) |
| `style={{ '--var': value }}` | Dynamic CSS variables only |
| Non-style consts | `TEST_ID`, `AUTOPLAY_MS`, labels, URLs — not Tailwind strings |
| Legacy files during migration | `*Classes.ts` / `componentShellClasses.ts` — **delete or inline** when the consuming component is in the current batch |

## Per-batch workflow (mandatory — no skip)

1. **Scope:** one component folder from the batch list only (or an agreed multi-batch range)
2. **Status:** set **In progress** in `docs/intralox-inline-tailwind-refactor-plan.md` before coding
3. **Inline:** move every class string onto the JSX element that uses it
4. **Delete:** remove class consts, `*Classes.ts`, utils class functions/maps from that folder
5. **Recheck** (run all; fix until clean):

```bash
cd headapps/intralox-sites

# No top-level class consts in touched folder
grep -rnE '^const [A-Z_][A-Z0-9_]* = ['\''"]' src/components/<folder> --include '*.tsx' | grep -iE 'class|flex|grid|text-|bg-|border-|rounded|gap-|items-|justify-|p-|m-|w-|h-|md:|lg:' || true

# No exported layout class consts in touched folder tsx
grep -rnE '^export const [A-Z_][A-Z0-9_]*(CLASS|Classes|_MAP)' src/components/<folder> --include '*.tsx' || true

# No *Classes.ts left in folder
find src/components/<folder> -name '*Classes.ts' | wc -l

# No class builders left in folder utils
grep -rnE 'export function \w*(Class|Classes|className)' src/components/<folder> --include '*Utils.ts' || true

npm run lint
```

6. **Status doc:** update **Current status** in `docs/intralox-inline-tailwind-refactor-plan.md` (summary table, batch row, iteration log, header date) — **mandatory before ending the session**

7. **Do not** start the next batch until recheck passes and status is updated

## PR checklist (each batch)

- [ ] Zero `*_CLASS` top-level consts in touched TSX
- [ ] Zero class maps / class builders in touched Utils
- [ ] Zero `*Classes.ts` in touched folder
- [ ] All `className` use inline literals or inline `cn()` on the node
- [ ] Lint + folder tests pass (when present)
- [ ] **Current status** updated in `docs/intralox-inline-tailwind-refactor-plan.md`
- [ ] Visual QA: 320, 768, 992, 1200px if layout changed

Referenced: `tailwind-only-styling.mdc`, `src/assets/base/variables.scss`, `docs/intralox-inline-tailwind-refactor-plan.md`
